I've just received word from DM International ( (P O Box 16188, Seattle, 
WA 98116-0188) who publishes Kinky People Places & Things and Bitches 
with Whips, that they have taken over Taste of Latex, and issue #10 is on 
the way.

> 
> What's behind this apparent mass exodus from SM-related publishing?
> I know it takes a lot of work and a considerable amount of cash, 
> and people burn out and magazines come and go, but lately it seems
> there a lot more going than coming...

It may be part of the burn-out cycle. And we're running out of fresh 
blood that is reckless enough to try to make a go ouf it.

However, I hear that Joseph Bean and some assocaites have picked up a 
small group of the Men's magazines (including, I think, "Bear") and are 
trying to make a go of it.

I'm one of the editors of Prometheus, which is published by The 
Eulenspiegel Society. We printed 72 pages last issue and sales outside 
our membership is growing.  But, if we had to pay for the time the staff 
put into getting the magazine together, it wouldn't fly.  It's done on a 
volunteer basis, and we're counting on a continuing flow of dedicated 
staff and contributors to make it work.

I'd like to do it for a living.  I don't think I can, so I won't quit my 
day job.

Leonard

