opinion about American criminal procedure recently, on occasion of the
Simpson case; I mean John H. Langbein.
                     ^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^
I would like to recommend, as further lecture *after* Fiorelli, his:

Prosecuting crime in the Renaissance, 1974 Cambridge: Harvard Univ. Press

Torture and the law of proof: Europe and England in the ancien regime,
1977 Chicago, Univ. of Chicago Press

Beste Gruesse undsoweiter,
Alexander Eichener

