torture literature, which all tends to be a little final, but nonetheless it's
intriguing stuff.  Eusebius' History of the Church (written around the fourth
century) has many crazed and quite fetishistic scenes involving big heartless
roman soldiers and wimpy christian martyrs...  Plus you can read it on the 
bus and everyone thinks you're a devoted catholic.  Feral House has also
published a book called Torments and Tortures of the Christian Martyrs by a
wonderfully troubled monk.  It's slow going, but fertile ground.
	Well, to end this poorly-written piece of mail, I should probably
mention that Harm's Way comes from a publisher called Twin Palms, in case
anyone wants to look for it.  It's awful pricey, but worth it to me.  Happy
reading.

