Guess I should mention Page DuBois' _Torture and Truth_ (Routledge I think,
around '89-91), which is tangentially related -- a discourse-oriented study
of the relationship between (you guessed it) torture and truth in ancient
Greece.  A very interesting and enlightening read if you're at all
interested in classics; she concludes that Western notions of "truth" have
their origins in the torture of slaves.

